cff-version: 1.2.0
message: "If you use this software, please cite it using the metadata below."
title: "Behavioral-laziness: least-action regularization of transfer-operator trajectories"
abstract: >-
  Self-contained numpy core and synthetic reproduction accompanying the paper
  "Recovering the transfer operator of a multicluster open system from aggregate
  data: the least-action principle on its trajectory" (informal name: "Behavioral
  Laziness"). The recovery of a transfer operator from two aggregate snapshots is
  severely under-determined, so the solution set is an affine manifold on which
  minimum-norm (Tikhonov) regularization is not neutral — it underestimates
  self-retention. This package implements the proposed least-action prior on the
  operator trajectory: null-space projection (hard, preserves the observed macro
  increment A·P exactly) and EWMA (soft), together with entropic optimal-transport
  baselines (Sinkhorn), an applicability phase map (delta × rho), and causal
  inner-CV selection of the regularization strength λ. All demos are deterministic
  (seeded) and CPU-only.
type: software
